<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="500" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1013,1181]" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1013,1038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Takada &amp; Momma, 1975" authorityName="Takada &amp; Momma" authorityYear="1975" box="[577,1052,1013,1037]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gombakana">
<emphasis box="[577,591,1014,1037]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[607,738,1013,1037]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">gombakana</emphasis>
(Takada &amp; Momma, 
<number box="[987,1044,1013,1037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="500" value="1975.0">1975</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1125,1228,1013,1037]" name="Malaysia" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(Malay Peninsula and Sabah) in the paramere and the vertical process of gonopods, the latter having small spines apicomedially (the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1085,1109]" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[291,452,1085,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gombakana">
<emphasis box="[291,452,1085,1109]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">P. gombakana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was checked by HW Chen), but can be distinguished from it by the aedeagal ventral bridges (termed inner paraphysis by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bachli" box="[563,771,1121,1145]" pageId="7" pageNumber="500" refString="Bachli, G., Vilela, C. R., Andersson, S. &amp; Saura, A. (2004) The Drosophilidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica. Vol. 39. Brill, Leiden, New York, 362 pp." type="book" year="2004">
Bächli 
<emphasis box="[644,701,1121,1145]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[715,771,1121,1145]" pageId="7" pageNumber="500" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) with 
<number box="[845,859,1121,1145]" pageId="7" pageNumber="500" value="2.0">2</number>
hook-shaped processes (basal and distal) each side (
<figureCitation box="[159,242,1157,1181]" captionStart="FIGURES 21, 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[170,1425,1261,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,1234,1948]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21, 22. Phortica (Phortica) ancistria Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 21. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 22. hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282320/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="500">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,242,1157,1181]" pageId="7" pageNumber="500" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
, pr).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
